        {
            "block_label": "table",
            "block_content": "<table><tr><td>Created By</td><td>Comment</td><td>Comment Date</td></tr><tr><td>MSANDERS</td><td>MUD PROGRAM: 0-400&#x27; Fresh Water; 400&#x27;-2400&#x27; Brine Water; 2400&#x27;-8500&#x27; Cut Brine; 8500&#x27;-11375&#x27; Cut Brine (lateral).</td><td>1/5/2010</td></tr><tr><td>MSANDERS</td><td>BOPE PROGRAM: 3000# psi system nippled up on 13 3/8&quot; and 9 5/8&quot; casing.</td><td>1/5/2010</td></tr><tr><td>MSANDERS</td><td>MAXIMUM ANTICIPATED BHP: 0-400&#x27; 191 PSI; 400&#x27;-2400&#x27; 1248 PSI; 2400&#x27;-8500&#x27; 4199 PSI. Depths are TVD.</td><td>1/5/2010</td></tr><tr><td>MSANDERS</td><td>Pilot hole drilled vertically to 8500&#x27;. Well will be plugged back with 400&#x27;-500&#x27; kick off plug at approx. 6483&#x27; and directionally drilled at 12 degrees per 100&#x27; with a 8 3/4&quot; hole to 7233&#x27; MD (6960&#x27; TVD). If hole conditions dictate, 7&quot; casing will be set.</td><td>1/5/2010</td></tr><tr><td>MSANDERS</td><td>A 6 1/8&quot; hole will then be drilled to 11375&#x27; MD (6960&#x27; TVD) where 4 1/2&quot; casing will be set and cemented. If 7&quot; casing is not set, then hole size will be reduced to 7 7/8&quot; and drilled to 11375&#x27; MD (6960&#x27; TVD) where 5 1/2&quot; casing will be set and cemented.</td><td>1/5/2010</td></tr><tr><td>MSANDERS</td><td>Penetration point of producing zone will be encountered at 660&#x27; FNL and 808&#x27; FEL, 15-25S-27E. Deepest TVD in the well is 8500&#x27; in the pilot hole. Deepest TVD in the lateral will be 6960&#x27;.</td><td>1/5/2010</td></tr><tr><td>MSANDERS</td><td>C-144; Casing Design Plan and Drilling Plan to follow by mail.</td><td>1/5/2010</td></tr></table>",
